# mount-drive config. One drive per line: KEY|MOUNTPOINT|DISPLAY_NAME
# Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
#
# KEY can be:
#   - a UUID         (stable for ext4, btrfs, ntfs, luks)
#   - LABEL:<label>  (use for vfat/exfat where the UUID is just a volume
#                     serial that changes on every reformat; case-sensitive,
#                     match what `lsblk -o LABEL,UUID` reports)
#
# MOUNTPOINT must exist on disk and be owned by you (the script will not create it).
#
# Examples:
# 4C6E97526E973424|/home/aditya/Media/Sanctuary|Sanctuary
# LABEL:ECHOSD|/home/aditya/Media/echoSD|echoSD
# LABEL:Music-backup|/home/aditya/Media/Music-backup|Music-backup
